               <floruit notBefore="1300" notAfter="1399">He was a saintly monk and contemporary of <persName ref="PRS1854Amdase">ʿAmda Ṣǝyon I</persName>. 
                  He is considered to have been the founder of the monastery of
                  <placeName ref="LOC4518Mandab">Mandābbā Madḫāne ʾAlam</placeName>.
                  He was one of the seven disciples of  
                  <persName ref="PRS6445Madhanin">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾabuna</roleName> Madḫānina ʾƎgziʾ</persName>.
                  He was the spritual father of <persName ref="PRS7598Nob">Nob</persName>, <persName ref="PRS3895estifano">ʾƎsṭifanos of Maqdasa Māryām</persName>, 
                  <persName ref="PRS8752senana">Ṣǝnʿana Krǝstos of Dabra Zayt</persName> and some others.</floruit>
             
